The paper proposes a new method for regularization in neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper also discusses the use of empirical Rademacher complexity, which is a measure of the complexity of a function class, and is commonly used in the analysis of learning algorithms. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
